  "event_preview": "Circuit de Monaco is a 3.337 km (2.074 mi) street circuit in Monte Carlo, Monaco, winding through the Principality with 19 corners and no run-off areas. The 2026 Monaco Grand Prix is the sixth round of the Formula One World Championship, held over 78 laps (260.286 km) on June 7. Kimi Antonelli leads the championship with 131 points, 43 points ahead of George Russell and 56 ahead of Charles Leclerc. Mercedes leads the constructors' championship with 219 points.\n\nAntonelli will be seeking to extend his perfect record at the circuit. Charles Leclerc, the home favourite, will attempt to add to his Monaco pedigree and prove Ferrari can be competitive on the demanding street circuit. Lewis Hamilton, now driving for Ferrari, brings his legendary Monaco record to the Scuderia. McLaren's Lando Norris will look to build on his recent form and redemption campaign after a challenging start to the season.\n\nThe fastest qualifying lap ever recorded at Monaco belongs to Lando Norris, who set a 1:09.954 during the 2025 qualifying session — the first sub-70 second lap in Monaco Grand Prix history. The official race lap record is held by Lewis Hamilton, who clocked a 1:10.166 during the 2024 race.",
